Raheem Sterling has returned “home” after swapping Manchester for London by signing for Chelsea on a five-year deal. He is the second player this summer to leave Manchester City for one of their 'big six' rivals after agreeing personal terms with Chelsea. Sterling has joined Chelsea with a wealth of accolades having won 12 major trophies with City including four of their eight league titles, five of their eight League Cups and one FA Cup. He leaves with 131 goals and 74 assists in 339 games across seven seasons following his move from Liverpool.